Changes in your view:
Add a hidden input to store the selected CategoryId:

html
Copy code
<input type="hidden" id="selectedCategoryId" value="0" />
Modify your showCategory function like this:

javascript
Copy code
function showCategory(categoryId) {
    $('#selectedCategoryId').val(categoryId);

    if (categoryId == 0) {
        $('.fs-5.fw-bold.text-primary').text('All');
    } else {
        var categoryName = $(`a[onclick="showCategory('${categoryId}')"]`).text();
        $('.fs-5.fw-bold.text-primary').text(categoryName);
    }

    // call ajax or load data based on categoryId here
}
Now, in your In Progress and Ready buttons, you can access the selected CategoryId like this:

html
Copy code
<button type="button" class="btn text-white text-center"
    onclick="handleStatus('InProgress')" 
    style="background-color: rgba(0, 102, 167, 1); border-color: rgba(0, 102, 167, 1);">
    In Progress
</button>

<button type="button" class="btn"
    onclick="handleStatus('Ready')" 
    style="background-color: white; border-color: rgba(0, 102, 167, 1); color: rgba(0, 102, 167, 1);">
    Ready
</button>
JavaScript function to get selected CategoryId:

javascript
Copy code
function handleStatus(status) {
    var categoryId = $('#selectedCategoryId').val();
    console.log("Selected CategoryId:", categoryId, "Status:", status);

    // You can call your ajax here for filter data
}
